3. Endpoints Summary

Resource	Endpoint	Method	Description

Projects	/projects/	GET, POST	List or create omics projects
	/projects/{id}/	GET, PUT, DELETE	Retrieve or modify a project
Samples	/samples/	GET, POST	List, filter, or create biological samples
	/samples/?project={id}	GET	List samples under a project
Files	/files/	GET, POST	Manage omics data file uploads
Sample Drafts	/sample-drafts/	GET, POST	Temporary sample entries before submission
Tissues	/tissues/	GET	List all tissue types or filter by kingdom
Organisms	/organisms/	GET	List cached organisms
Organism Search	/organisms/search/?q=<term>&kingdom=<optional>	GET	Live taxonomy-aware search
File Upload (direct)	/upload/	POST	Upload a file tied to a sample ID



