4. Example Usage

4.1 Create a New Project

curl -X POST https://omics.reslab.dev/api/projects/ \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "Banana Genome Profiling",
    "description": "RNA-seq and DNA-seq data for Musa spp."
  }'


---

4.2 Add a Sample

curl -X POST https://omics.reslab.dev/api/samples/ \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "sample_id": "Musa_leaf_RNA_001",
    "project": 2,
    "organism": 15,
    "tissue_type": 8,
    "data_type": "RNA",
    "collected_on": "2025-11-09"
  }'


---

4.3 Upload an Omics Data File

curl -X POST https://omics.reslab.dev/api/files/ \
  -F "sample=10" \
  -F "file_type=FASTQ" \
  -F "file=@/path/to/Musa_RNA_001.fastq.gz"


---

4.4 Search for an Organism (Live)

curl "https://omics.reslab.dev/api/organisms/search/?q=musa"

Example output:

[
  {
    "id": 15,
    "scientific_name": "Musa acuminata",
    "common_name": "Banana",
    "kingdom": "Plant",
    "taxonomy_id": 4641
  }
]


